User characteristics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Actors
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:Actors"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Visitor / Unregistered User:
\emph default
 a person who installed the SafeStreets application but never registered
 to the service.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

He can only view a brief explanation of the application's functions and
 proceed with the registration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
User / Registered User
\emph default
: a person who executed the whole registration procedure, providing necessary
 information and confirming its registration by following the link in a
 confirmation email.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

He can log to his user account though the application to access all of the
 functionalities it provides to normal users without particular permissions.
 This means he can send a violation report and view its previous violations,
 view information on streets with the most reports.
 He can't view reports submitted by other users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Administrator:
\emph default
 SafeStreets employee whose role is to manually manage user accounts (for
 example by assigning or removing roles and permissions).
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

They can access a dedicated web backend to carry out these operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Officers / Authority:
\emph default
 police officer or other type of municipality employee involved with SafeStreets
' activity.
 He can independently sign up for an account through the application, and
 request its Officer permissions to be granted by an Administrator in a
 second moment.
 Alternatively, the municipality can ask SafeStreets to make an Administrator
 create its account with relevant permissions already set.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Besides being able to use every feature offered to Registered Users through
 the mobile application, he can also view reports sent by any user.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Authorities can also access a web backend provided by SafeStreets to easily
 browse the whole reports dataset and get statistical data about it.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Can view sender data?
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Municipality:
\emph default
 entity represented by the local authorities, which provides data through
 API endpoints and receives data form SafeStreets through different API
 endpoints.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Offender:
\emph default
 a person who is responsible for a violation, for example the person who
 parked their car in a forbidden area or exceeded the speed limit while
 driving.
\end_layout

